 it keeps a cache </w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidR="00E661CB"><w:t xml:space="preserve">locally on the laptop/workstation </w:t></w:r><w:r><w:t>of filed emails. This Cache purpose appears to be for offline searching and retrieval of filed emails. The problem is your p</w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidR="00E661CB"><w:t xml:space="preserve">otentially </w:t></w:r><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">storing gigabyes of emails locally on the device just to enable this. </w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w:rsidR="00E776D3" w:rsidRDefault="00E776D3"><w:r><w:t>The search function. Does this keep an index of some sort</w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidR="00E661CB"><w:t>?</w:t></w:r><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve"> to index the filed emails to enable fast search or does it just search the filed email locations and email headers/contents one by one. I thiking of speed of search here over 1000’s of email how quick will this be?</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w:rsidR="00E776D3" w:rsidRDefault="00E776D3"><w:r><w:t>In the search Settings:</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w:rsidR="00E776D3" w:rsidRDefault="00E776D3"><w:r><w:rPr><w:noProof/><w:lang w:eastAsia="en-GB"/></w:rPr><w:drawing><wp:inline distT="0" distB="0" distL="0" distR="0" wp14:anchorId="4BD44608" wp14:editId="141DBCF7"><wp:extent cx="5731510" cy="3562985"/><wp:effectExtent l="0" t="0" r="2540" b="0"/><wp:docPr id="1" name="Picture 1"/><wp:cNvGraphicFramePr><a:graphicFrameLocks xmlns:a="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/main" noChangeAspect="1"/></wp:cNvGraphicFramePr><a:graphic xmlns:a="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/main"><a:graphicData uri="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/picture"><pic:pic xmlns:pic="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/picture"><pic:nvPicPr><pic:cNvPr id="1" name=""/><pic:cNvPicPr/></pic:nvPicPr><pic:blipFill><a:blip r:embed="rId6"/><a:stretch><a:fillRect/></a:stretch></pic:blipFill><pic:spPr><a:xfrm><a:off x="0" y="0"/><a:ext cx="5731510" cy="3562985"/></a:xfrm><a:prstGeom prst="rect"><a:avLst/></a:prst